		{
			"id": "ALAS2UNBOUND-1.17-2024-002",
			"title": "Amazon Linux 2 - Unbound-1.17 2.0 - ALAS2UNBOUND-1.17-2024-002: important priority package update for unbound",
			"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2 - Unbound-1.17 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2024-1488:\n\tA vulnerability was found in Unbound due to incorrect default permissions, allowing any process outside the unbound group to modify the unbound runtime configuration. If a process can connect over localhost to port 8953, it can alter the configuration of unbound.service. This flaw allows an unprivileged attacker to manipulate a running instance, potentially altering forwarders, allowing them to track all queries forwarded by the local resolver, and, in some cases, disrupting resolving altogether.\n",
